quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  60,12,"O Prophet! When believing women come to you giving you a pledge that they will not associate aught with Allah, and will not steal, and will not commit fornication, and will not kill their children, and will not bring a calumny which they have forged of th"
  60,13,O you who believe! Do not make friends with a people with whom Allah is wroth; indeed they despair of the Hereafter as the unbelievers despair of those in the graves
  61,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth declares the glory of Allah; and He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  61,2,O you who believe! Why do you say that which you do not do
  61,3,It is most hateful to Allah that you should say that which you do not do
  61,4,Surely Allah loves those who fight (or strive) in His way in ranks as if they were a firm and compact wall
  61,5,"And when Moses said to his people, \"O my people! Why do you vex me, though you know that I am the Messenger of Allah to you?\" But when they turned away, Allah made their heart go astray, and Allah does not guide transgressing people"